The paper deals with privacy risks in social network datasets and graph anonymization techniques, which are relevant to several sub-categories in computer science. Specifically, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as it directly relates to the study of social network datasets. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses privacy risks and attacks on anonymized graphs. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases) are relevant as the paper discusses the structural properties of graphs and their anonymization. Finally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses machine learning-based techniques for de-anonymization.
